title: For Sale:  Molot VEPR FIME Import - FM-AK47-21 Sidefolder - VPR-76239 - 7.62x39mm AK
postcontent: This rifle is a Molot VEPR, imported and converted by the FIME Group. It is equipped with a sidefolding stock similar to the VEPR-12 shotguns from the factory, with a swappable cheekrest to aid in using optics if desired. This is the FM-AK47-21, a model released in the Spring of 2017. Molot imports were banned under US sanctions on Russia in June of 2017. Not very many of these rifles were imported as a result. It fires 7.62x39mm and, like all VEPRs, built upon the more durable RPK receivers (RPKs are the Russian LMG and feature 1.5x thicker receivers, reinforced bulged front trunnions, and heavier barrels). It has a 16.5" barrel with the standard left-hand threading for AKs.Right now, Atlantic and K-Var both list this model on their websites for 1600 USD new. Atlantic is out of stock. As there will be no further imports, it is unlikely you will find a new rifle anywhere else for a better price (and if you do, you should consider purchasing it).This rifle is in very good condition. I purchased it only a week or so before the sanctions were put in place, so I have maintained it in as good a condition I can while testing the rifle. I estimate ~500 rounds have been fired in this rifle. I have swapped the handguards with a cheesegrater and metal VEPR rail, but retained the stock guards so that one can return it to stock configuration with little hassle. I have also put on a muzzle device. All these items can be found on AKOU's store if you wish further details. They are:Vepr FM M-Lok Rail (99.99)AKM/AK-74/Vepr-12 Length Cheese Grater Upper Handguard (39.99)BD2-AK47 Muzzle Brake (54.99)Included is the factory 5 round magazine, as well as 3 surplus Yugo magazines with bolt-hold-open followers and a Polish RADOM surplus magazine that matches the finish quite nicely. I have also kept the cleaning kit and the box the rifle came in. I am selling the rifle as I found I do not love AKs. They are fun rifles, but from a practical standpoint it is difficult to argue with a well-built AR. I'll perhaps have another some day, but a scarce and high quality AK like this VEPR deserves a home with someone who will truly appreciate it. Additional images are available upon request. I am willing to ship the rifle, but buyer must pay for shipping costs and only money orders will be accepted. In-person transactions will only be conducted with Nebraska residents with up-to-date ID and Purchasing or Concealed Carry Permits.

title: For Sale:  Are Cryptocurrency wallets secure?
postcontent:
Cryptocurrency Wallets are safe and secure to differing levels. The level of protection depends upon the kind of wallet you utilize (desktop computer, mobile, online, paper, hardware) and also the service provider. An internet server is an inherently riskier atmosphere to maintain your money as compared to offline. On the internet wallets could expose users to possible vulnerabilities in the wallet system which could be manipulated by cyberpunks to swipe your funds.
Keep in mind that despite which best cryptocurrency wallet you utilize, losing your private keys will certainly lead you to lose your money.
Back-up your wallet:- Store only small amounts of money for daily usage online, on your computer system or mobile, maintaining the huge bulk of your funds in a high safety and security environment.
Update software:- Maintain your software approximately day to ensure that you have the most recent safety and security improvements available. You need to routinely upgrade not just your wallet software however also the software on your computer system or mobile.
Include additional security layers:- Use wallets that have an excellent reputation as well as offer additional protection layers like two-factor verification and also extra pin code needs whenever a wallet application obtains opened. You might also intend to consider a wallet that provides multi-signature transactions like Armory or Copay. A multi-signature wallet needs the authorization of another user or users before a transaction could be made.

title: For Sale:  Smith & Wesson 439 ASP 9mm Custom RARE
postcontent: They only made about 250 of these 439 ASP's and they are like hens teeth! The ASP was truly the gun design that launched the compact tactical handgun! Designed in the 1960s by Paris Theodore, abstract artist, holster maker and (self-proclaimed) CIA independent contractor, the ASP takes a basic Smith & Wesson pistol (a Model 439 in this case) and "remanufactures" it into an ideal defensive carry pistol, optimized for long term concealment and rapid deployment. During the process the pistol is shortened, edges rounded and smooth, hammer bobbed, the trigger guard trimmed on the right side and the sights replaced with a one-piece "Guttersnipe" sighting plane. The grips are transparent Lexan with matching cutouts in the magazine to permit assessment of remaining ammunition. Included with the pistol is one magazine, the factory ASP leather holster and a copy of the owners manual.
